steps.description:
The Washi tape can be added in various ways:
Place strips from the top of the egg to the bottom of the egg. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/1/11/Make-Washi-Tape-Eggs-Step-2Bullet1.jpg/v4-459px-Make-Washi-Tape-Eggs-Step-2Bullet1.jpg","bigUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/1/11/Make-Washi-Tape-Eggs-Step-2Bullet1.jpg/v4-759px-Make-Washi-Tape-Eggs-Step-2Bullet1.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":306,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":506.31868131868134,"licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}

Place the strips around the middle of the egg. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/1/10/Make-Washi-Tape-Eggs-Step-2Bullet2.jpg/v4-459px-Make-Washi-Tape-Eggs-Step-2Bullet2.jpg","bigUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/1/10/Make-Washi-Tape-Eggs-Step-2Bullet2.jpg/v4-759px-Make-Washi-Tape-Eggs-Step-2Bullet2.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":306,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":506.31868131868134,"licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}

Place the strips around the middle of the egg and other strips from top to bottom of the egg, to make a cross effect. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/7/73/Make-Washi-Tape-Eggs-Step-2Bullet3.jpg/v4-459px-Make-Washi-Tape-Eggs-Step-2Bullet3.jpg","bigUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/7/73/Make-Washi-Tape-Eggs-Step-2Bullet3.jpg/v4-759px-Make-Washi-Tape-Eggs-Step-2Bullet3.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":306,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":506.31868131868134,"licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}

Place the strips diagonally across the egg. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/8/81/Make-Washi-Tape-Eggs-Step-2Bullet4.jpg/v4-459px-Make-Washi-Tape-Eggs-Step-2Bullet4.jpg","bigUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/8/81/Make-Washi-Tape-Eggs-Step-2Bullet4.jpg/v4-759px-Make-Washi-Tape-Eggs-Step-2Bullet4.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":306,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":506.31868131868134,"licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}

Wrap the egg like a mummy, or any which way. This is ideal for young children; let them do it however they fancy. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/1/1c/Make-Washi-Tape-Eggs-Step-2Bullet5.jpg/v4-459px-Make-Washi-Tape-Eggs-Step-2Bullet5.jpg","bigUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/1/1c/Make-Washi-Tape-Eggs-Step-2Bullet5.jpg/v4-759px-Make-Washi-Tape-Eggs-Step-2Bullet5.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":306,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":506.31868131868134,"licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}

Try drawing designs on paper and using small pieces of Washi tape on the paper if you're not quite sure what you'll like. When you're happy with the design choice, proceed to the next part. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/f/f1/Make-Washi-Tape-Eggs-Step-3.jpg/v4-459px-Make-Washi-Tape-Eggs-Step-3.jpg","bigUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/f/f1/Make-Washi-Tape-Eggs-Step-3.jpg/v4-759px-Make-Washi-Tape-Eggs-Step-3.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":306,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":506.31868131868134,"licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}
